00:29:23.622 --> 00:29:26.757
You could put him
in a home or something


497
00:29:27.626 --> 00:29:29.726
or hiring home caring.

498
00:29:32.564 --> 00:29:35.565
I thought about it. But I got my
reasons for keeping him around.


499
00:29:37.770 --> 00:29:39.770
You're always so guarded.

500
00:29:41.540 --> 00:29:42.506
I guess.

501
00:29:42.508 --> 00:29:46.676
It's just weird I've
never even met him.


502
00:29:46.678 --> 00:29:48.779
That's because I like you.

503
00:30:11.603 --> 00:30:13.103
You're smaller?

504
00:30:15.374 --> 00:30:18.408
I'm trying to create something
big and you're getting smaller?


505
00:30:21.814 --> 00:30:23.313
What are you telling me?

506
00:30:27.219 --> 00:30:28.685
I don't know what
else to feed you.


507
00:30:31.223 --> 00:30:32.703
I'd kick your ass
if you even had one.


508
00:30:37.629 --> 00:30:38.728
No!

509
00:30:43.202 --> 00:30:46.470
Yeah.

510
00:30:46.472 --> 00:30:48.171
- <i>Hi, Mitch.</i>
- Natalie.


511
00:30:48.173 --> 00:30:50.607
How nice of you to call again.

512
00:30:50.609 --> 00:30:53.877
I'm just calling to congratulate
you on a great event.


513
00:30:53.879 --> 00:30:55.112
I'm sure.

514
00:30:55.114 --> 00:30:56.646
But while I have
you on the phone,


515
00:30:56.648 --> 00:30:58.448
is there any chance we could get

516
00:30:58.450 --> 00:31:01.751
a first few chapters
of the novel by the weekend?


517
00:31:03.555 --> 00:31:04.754
That wasn't the deal.

518
00:31:04.756 --> 00:31:06.523
I know, I know
it wasn't the deal,


519
00:31:06.525 --> 00:31:09.359
but I'd like to do things a bit
differently this time around,


520
00:31:09.361 --> 00:31:13.363
so we can avoid those instances
of being perpetually late.


521
00:31:14.500 --> 00:31:16.166
No need to beat around the bush.

522
00:31:16.168 --> 00:31:17.601
<i>I know, I'm just saying</i>

523
00:31:17.603 --> 00:31:20.203
that I don't want
to be late on this project.


524
00:31:20.205 --> 00:31:21.404
This is going to be the one

525
00:31:21.406 --> 00:31:24.441
that's gonna take you
way over the top.


526
00:31:24.443 --> 00:31:28.145
Yeah, I know, I want it to.

527
00:31:28.147 --> 00:31:29.713
Then we are on
the same page then?


528
00:31:30.516 --> 00:31:32.916
I'll see what I can
do over the weekend.


529
00:31:32.918 --> 00:31:34.484
<i>Great. That's good.</i>

530
00:31:55.307 --> 00:31:56.307
Fuck it.

531
00:32:02.247 --> 00:32:04.681
I know you get
this all the time.


532
00:32:04.683 --> 00:32:06.683
That's okay, go for it.

533
00:32:06.685 --> 00:32:08.919
Where do you get your ideas?

534
00:32:08.921 --> 00:32:12.822
Things happen to me and then
I exaggerate for effect.


535
00:32:14.426 --> 00:32:18.295
How many shitty people could you
possibly have left to forgive?


536
00:32:18.297 --> 00:32:21.498
Self-development is
a lifelong process.


537
00:32:21.500 --> 00:32:22.666
I guess.

538
00:32:22.668 --> 00:32:26.836
Don't worry, I don't have
anything against you... yet.


539
00:32:28.607 --> 00:32:30.440
You're funny.

540
00:32:30.442 --> 00:32:33.910
♫♫♫

541
00:32:40.452 --> 00:32:41.651
Mm.

542
00:32:44.690 --> 00:32:45.855
Let me look at you.

543
00:32:47.559 --> 00:32:48.959
Well?

544
00:32:48.961 --> 00:32:50.227
You're gorgeous, Mary.

545
00:33:05.010 --> 00:33:06.710
Uh...

546
00:33:06.712 --> 00:33:07.644
What you looking at?

547
00:33:07.646 --> 00:33:10.013
Sorry. I'm nosey.

548
00:33:10.015 --> 00:33:11.715
It's okay.

549
00:33:11.717 --> 00:33:12.717
You know...

550
00:33:14.319 --> 00:33:16.319
I thought I could be
a writer someday.


551
00:33:17.556 --> 00:33:18.855
Something special.

552
00:33:20.359 --> 00:33:21.591
I guess I just didn't
have the gift.


553
00:33:21.593 --> 00:33:24.461
Gift, curse, call it
wherever you like.


554
00:33:25.264 --> 00:33:27.831
- Don't be so dramatic.
- I know, I'm sorry.


555
00:33:29.835 --> 00:33:32.936
My latest book is
just missing something.


556
00:33:33.905 --> 00:33:36.306
It's like you never know
exactly what it takes.


557
00:33:36.308 --> 00:33:38.308
It takes a lot
out of you, doesn't it?


558
00:33:39.911 --> 00:33:42.545
Yeah. Nobody ever gets that.

559
00:33:49.755 --> 00:33:51.721
I don't like people
very close to me.


560
00:33:52.724 --> 00:33:54.691
This is why my last
relationship failed.


561
00:33:55.861 --> 00:33:59.396
This job requires
a certain type of isolation.


562
00:33:59.398 --> 00:34:02.899
Well, you must be
doing something right.


563
00:34:02.901 --> 00:34:05.335
Maybe. I have my regrets.

564
00:34:06.605 --> 00:34:07.605
Who doesn't?

565
00:34:10.042 --> 00:34:11.408
You wanna go upstairs?

566
00:34:14.379 --> 00:34:15.445
Yeah.

567
00:34:19.051 --> 00:34:22.552
♫♫♫

568
00:34:32.998 --> 00:34:35.598
- There's really a dog in there?
- Yeah.


569
00:34:45.911 --> 00:34:49.512
What is that?

570
00:34:53.385 --> 00:34:54.517
I'm sorry, Mary.

571
00:35:19.111 --> 00:35:20.977
This isn't a story,
these are notes.


572
00:35:20.979 --> 00:35:22.645
What you got, writer's
block or something?


573
00:35:24.883 --> 00:35:26.483
Not enough is right.

574
00:35:31.456 --> 00:35:33.890
Fuck you. I liked her.

575
00:35:33.892 --> 00:35:36.493
I kept up my end of the bargain.
You give me what she is worth.


576
00:35:38.930 --> 00:35:41.564
Make all the sound you want.
This is the last straw.


577
00:35:41.566 --> 00:35:42.799
I'll finish this book on my own

578
00:35:42.801 --> 00:35:44.534
like I should have
from the beginning.


579
00:36:20.605 --> 00:36:24.674
♫♫♫

580
00:36:43.862 --> 00:36:48.565
♫♫♫

581
00:36:48.567 --> 00:36:51.067
Hey, Sophie, it's me.

582
00:36:52.871 --> 00:36:55.872
Just wanted to talk.
I'm having kind of a bad night.


583
00:36:57.642 --> 00:37:00.176
<i>Anyways, call me back.</i>

584
00:37:01.680 --> 00:37:03.079
<i>Love you.</i>

585
00:37:03.081 --> 00:37:08.485
♫♫♫

586
00:37:20.765 --> 00:37:22.699
Mitch Stockridge?

587
00:37:22.701 --> 00:37:24.234
Nope. I think you're mistaken.

588
00:37:24.236 --> 00:37:27.136
You are not Mitch Stockridge,
bestselling author,


589
00:37:27.138 --> 00:37:29.772
whose picture hangs
in every local bookstore?


590
00:37:29.774 --> 00:37:32.442
Nope.

591
00:37:32.443 --> 00:37:35.111
Without that cheesy get-up,
you'll look just like him.


592
00:37:35.113 --> 00:37:37.514
- Well, I'm...
- Mr. Stockridge,


593
00:37:37.516 --> 00:37:39.549
I have a few questions
about Luke Rousseau.


594
00:37:41.052 --> 00:37:43.286
Alright. What do
you want to know?


595
00:37:43.288 --> 00:37:47.590
Well, I'm told he came to visit
you and then he never came home.


596
00:37:47.592 --> 00:37:48.691
That's not my problem.

597
00:37:49.895 --> 00:37:53.129
- You two had a history.
- You can say that.


598
00:37:53.131 --> 00:37:54.664
What, did he visit you?

599
00:37:54.666 --> 00:37:56.199
He did and then he left.

600
00:37:56.201 --> 00:37:58.301
What did you discuss?

601
00:37:58.303 --> 00:38:00.203
Nothing really. 
Just caught up.

602
00:38:00.205 --> 00:38:01.771
Hadn't seen him
since high-school.


603
00:38:02.574 --> 00:38:03.640
He liked the new book.

604
00:38:03.642 --> 00:38:07.710
Did he happen to mention where
he was headed after he left?


605
00:38:07.712 --> 00:38:09.279
Look, I'll save
you some digging.


606
00:38:10.549 --> 00:38:11.915
I never liked the guy much.

607
00:38:13.051 --> 00:38:15.051
And if you ask anybody
that knew us twenty years ago,


608
00:38:15.053 --> 00:38:16.686
they'll tell you the same thing.

609
00:38:16.688 --> 00:38:20.823
I wanted him gone... back then.

610
00:38:20.825 --> 00:38:23.693
We've moved on, all of us.

611
00:38:23.695 --> 00:38:26.229
And if that's all you have,
you wouldn't know how much.


612
00:38:26.231 --> 00:38:29.699
So, if you'll excuse me,
I am a little busy right now.


613
00:38:29.701 --> 00:38:31.251
Well, I understand that,

614
00:38:31.252 --> 00:38:32.802
but I still have a few
questions for you, Sir.


615
00:38:32.804 --> 00:38:35.238
What makes you think that I
even remember where he went?


616
00:38:35.240 --> 00:38:37.407
That was weeks ago.

617
00:38:37.408 --> 00:38:39.575
You never know.
They say writers are observant.


618
00:38:41.913 --> 00:38:44.080
I'm sorry I bothered you,
Mr. Stockridge.


619
00:38:44.082 --> 00:38:45.882
- Thank you for your time.
- You're welcome.


620
00:38:48.753 --> 00:38:52.021
If you hear anything else,
give me a call.


621
00:38:52.023 --> 00:38:54.123
Detective Abigail Dunn.

622
00:38:54.125 --> 00:38:55.191
I prefer Abby.

623
00:38:57.228 --> 00:39:00.863
My ex-husband used to read
your inspirational stories.


624
00:39:00.865 --> 00:39:02.699
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.


625
00:39:02.701 --> 00:39:05.134
- Happy to help.
- I didn't say they helped.


626
00:39:05.937 --> 00:39:09.038
All right.
Have a good one.


627
00:39:37.369 --> 00:39:38.668
Hello, Natalie.

628
00:39:38.670 --> 00:39:40.036
<i>Yeah, I saw the covers.</i>

629
00:39:40.038 --> 00:39:41.404
We haven't said anything.

630
00:39:41.406 --> 00:39:43.006
Be a lot easier
to get through things


631
00:39:43.008 --> 00:39:44.641
if I stopped
getting interrupted.


632
00:39:44.643 --> 00:39:46.909
I'm gonna pretend you're
referring to other people.


633
00:39:46.911 --> 00:39:49.812
Well, I could choose
a cover if I had a book.


634
00:39:49.814 --> 00:39:52.148
And it's kind of hard for us
to come up with a cover


635
00:39:52.150 --> 00:39:54.150
when we haven't got a book yet.

636
00:39:54.152 --> 00:39:56.219
Can we just slow things
down a little bit right now?


637
00:39:56.221 --> 00:39:57.920
I'm kind of going
through something here.


638
00:39:57.922 --> 00:40:00.690
Oh, Mitch,
you made a commitment.


639
00:40:00.692 --> 00:40:02.892
<i>You're gonna have
to live with it.</i>


640
00:40:11.903 --> 00:40:13.836
Yeah, go fuck yourself.

641
00:40:20.278 --> 00:40:24.414
I didn't peg you to be a reader
of self-help books, Detective.


642
00:40:26.418 --> 00:40:28.785
I tried to see what it would
give me on Luke Rousseau.


643
00:40:28.787 --> 00:40:31.021
It wasn't much.

644
00:40:31.022 --> 00:40:33.256
- Well, maybe Logan was right.
- Maybe.


645
00:40:33.258 --> 00:40:36.793
Well, in any event, I hope
you like missing person cases


646
00:40:36.795 --> 00:40:38.728
- because I've got another one.
- Let me guess.


647
00:40:38.730 --> 00:40:40.763
Another drunk college kid
on daddy's boat.


648
00:40:40.765 --> 00:40:42.131
You wish.

649
00:40:42.133 --> 00:40:45.201
This one is a sad story.
A woman named Mary.


650
00:40:45.203 --> 00:40:47.036
Christ.

651
00:40:47.038 --> 00:40:49.172
- Any leads?
- Nothing so far.


652
00:40:49.174 --> 00:40:51.374
I guess there's no
justice in this world.


653
00:40:51.376 --> 00:40:54.377
If you find any, make sure
the front desk knows.


654
00:40:59.984 --> 00:41:01.451
Okay.

655
00:41:01.453 --> 00:41:03.186
I propose a toast right now

656
00:41:03.188 --> 00:41:05.121
to the best first draft

657
00:41:05.123 --> 00:41:09.225
of the best novel
since Jane Eyre.


658
00:41:10.462 --> 00:41:12.261
Please don't laugh.

659
00:41:12.263 --> 00:41:14.897
- Don't. It's insulting.
- Jane Eyre?


660
00:41:14.899 --> 00:41:17.233
It's literally the only novel
I can think of at the time.


661
00:41:17.235 --> 00:41:19.035
Did you google books
just to drop that one?


662
00:41:19.037 --> 00:41:21.270
Okay, I like Jane Eyre,
I have a feminine side.


663
00:41:22.107 --> 00:41:24.140
What? Stop.

664
00:41:24.142 --> 00:41:25.475
Cheers, Nick.

665
00:41:25.477 --> 00:41:27.877
Now I know why are you
over here all the damn time.


666
00:41:27.879 --> 00:41:30.747
I haven't toked like this
since grad school.


667
00:41:30.749 --> 00:41:32.048
- Did she say toked?
- Mm-Hm.


668
00:41:32.050 --> 00:41:33.783
Is that the word
she just used, "toked"?


669
00:41:33.785 --> 00:41:35.351
I've never heard my wife
use that word before.


670
00:41:35.353 --> 00:41:37.420
- My classy, classy wife.
- Hey.


671
00:41:37.422 --> 00:41:39.355
I'm allowed to have
a masculine side.


672
00:41:39.357 --> 00:41:40.389
Yes, you are.

673
00:41:40.391 --> 00:41:42.859
Mm. I'm out.

674
00:41:42.861 --> 00:41:44.227
Let me get you another
one real quick.


675
00:41:44.229 --> 00:41:45.962
Fresh out.
I'm gonna go make a run.


676
00:41:45.964 --> 00:41:47.430
Not like this, you're not.

677
00:41:47.432 --> 00:41:49.065
It's a few beers. I'm fine.

678
00:41:49.067 --> 00:41:50.299
Mitch, don't.

679
00:41:50.301 --> 00:41:51.768
You two have fun.

680
00:41:53.171 --> 00:41:54.971
Drive safe, buddy.

681
00:41:59.110 --> 00:42:01.010
He can't just go on like this.

682
00:42:02.046 --> 00:42:03.846
There's nothing
I can do for him. I know.


683
00:42:03.848 --> 00:42:05.314
It's not your job.

684
00:42:05.316 --> 00:42:06.516
You can't just
take care of him...


685
00:42:06.518 --> 00:42:08.251
I know. Listen, okay?

686
00:42:08.253 --> 00:42:10.186
You are not there when
the crowds are there


687
00:42:10.188 --> 00:42:12.388
and the parties, everybody is
gushing over the guy, okay?


688
00:42:12.390 --> 00:42:13.523
I'm there in the alone time

689
00:42:13.525 --> 00:42:16.559
and I see how he is
and how he acts.


690
00:42:16.561 --> 00:42:18.261
While I'm sitting home alone?

691
00:42:18.263 --> 00:42:19.796
You don't have
to sit home alone.


692
00:42:19.798 --> 00:42:21.297
You go out have
girl time if you want.


693
00:42:21.299 --> 00:42:24.267
- Okay, thank you very much.
- Okay, I'm sorry. I'm sorry.


694
00:42:24.269 --> 00:42:26.369
Okay, listen, right?

695
00:42:26.371 --> 00:42:27.503
Mitch is my best friend.

696
00:42:27.505 --> 00:42:30.540
He is just going through
a rough period right now, okay?


697
00:42:30.542 --> 00:42:31.808
That's it.

698
00:42:33.812 --> 00:42:35.344
He brings it on himself.

699
00:42:36.147 --> 00:42:38.147
He is never happy.

700
00:42:40.251 --> 00:42:41.417
Yeah, I know he is not.

701
00:42:57.502 --> 00:42:59.836
Small world. Hi there.

702
00:43:02.006 --> 00:43:04.073
You followed me
to the store, really?


703
00:43:05.944 --> 00:43:08.177
I'm not here on business,
Mr. Stockridge.


704
00:43:08.179 --> 00:43:10.446
Contrary to what you
may have seen on TV,


705
00:43:10.448 --> 00:43:13.382
cops do not subsist
exclusively on donuts.


706
00:43:13.384 --> 00:43:15.885
Are you denying that you
like donuts, Detective?


707
00:43:15.887 --> 00:43:18.221
Don't be ridiculous.
They are delicious.


708
00:43:18.223 --> 00:43:20.590
- Excuse me, Mr. Stockridge.
- Oh, hi.


709
00:43:20.592 --> 00:43:23.159
Hi. I can't believe it.

710
00:43:23.161 --> 00:43:25.328
- I'm your biggest fan. Do you...
- Yes.


711
00:43:25.330 --> 00:43:27.930
- Do you think you could?
- Yes, of course.


712
00:43:33.004 --> 00:43:34.136
Thank you so much.

713
00:43:34.138 --> 00:43:35.354
You're welcome.

714
00:43:35.355 --> 00:43:36.635
Your book saved
my friend's life.


715
00:43:40.979 --> 00:43:42.311
Wow.

716
00:43:42.313 --> 00:43:45.548
You saved a life.
Not many authors can say that.


717
00:43:45.550 --> 00:43:46.616
What do you want?

718
00:43:46.618 --> 00:43:48.951
Nothing. I promise.

719
00:43:48.953 --> 00:43:53.289
Although, since we are
both here shopping for juice,


720
00:43:53.291 --> 00:43:56.292
I will confess I do have
a few more questions.


721
00:43:56.294 --> 00:43:58.294
Doesn't mean I'm gonna
have any more answers.


722
00:43:58.296 --> 00:44:01.030
- Not about Luke Rousseau.
- Oh.


723
00:44:01.032 --> 00:44:02.465
You were recently
seen having drinks


724
00:44:02.467 --> 00:44:04.233
with a woman named Mary Rollins.

725
00:44:04.235 --> 00:44:06.168
I can provide you with
the date, time and location


726
00:44:06.170 --> 00:44:07.470
if that would refresh
your memory.


727
00:44:07.472 --> 00:44:10.072
I remember. Nice girl.

728
00:44:10.074 --> 00:44:14.343
Well, it was bar, so eyewitness
memories are predictively fuzzy.


729
00:44:14.345 --> 00:44:16.145
No one can be sure
they saw her leave.


730
00:44:16.147 --> 00:44:18.481
- I was wondering if you did.
- Can't help you.


731
00:44:18.483 --> 00:44:20.350
So, we done here?

732
00:44:20.351 --> 00:44:22.218
Another person is missing,
Mr. Stockridge.


733
00:44:22.220 --> 00:44:23.953
Most people might express

734
00:44:23.955 --> 00:44:26.255
little more interest
in the situation you're at.


735
00:44:26.257 --> 00:44:27.257
Leave me alone.

736
00:44:29.427 --> 00:44:30.459
Suit yourself.

737
00:44:31.596 --> 00:44:33.396
Enjoy your day.

738
00:44:35.466 --> 00:44:37.783
Oh, Detective,

739
00:44:37.784 --> 00:44:40.101
I just remembered donuts
are on aisle nine, FYI.


740
00:44:54.419 --> 00:44:55.451
Got a treat for you.

741
00:44:57.588 --> 00:44:59.288
That's just poison.

742
00:44:59.290 --> 00:45:00.530
What are you, a health nut now?

743
00:45:01.693 --> 00:45:03.092
What you got to live
for anyways?


744
00:45:03.094 --> 00:45:04.360
Who are those people downstairs?

745
00:45:04.362 --> 00:45:06.329
It's Nick and Laura.

746
