Thank you.

998
01:03:40.377 --> 01:03:43.078
Thanks for bailing me out, man.

999
01:03:44.081 --> 01:03:45.580
Do we need to go
get your car now?


1000
01:03:46.383 --> 01:03:47.682
I'll take care
of it in the morning.


1001
01:03:47.684 --> 01:03:51.853
God, Mitch, this Sophie thing
must have you really fucked up


1002
01:03:51.855 --> 01:03:53.388
if you're picking up hookers.

1003
01:03:56.359 --> 01:04:00.128
I was gonna kill her
and hope nobody would notice.


1004
01:04:00.130 --> 01:04:02.230
It's good. You should keep
that charming sense of humor,


1005
01:04:02.232 --> 01:04:03.565
it's getting you far.

1006
01:04:03.567 --> 01:04:06.201
I'm fucking drained.

1007
01:04:06.203 --> 01:04:09.237
You know, I wasn't gonna say
anything but you look like shit.


1008
01:04:09.239 --> 01:04:10.338
I was in jail.

1009
01:04:10.340 --> 01:04:11.506
I know.

1010
01:04:11.508 --> 01:04:13.741
And I hope you've
made a lot of friends,


1011
01:04:13.743 --> 01:04:16.778
friends you can confide in,
talk to, you know.


1012
01:04:18.281 --> 01:04:19.681
I feel like shit.

1013
01:04:21.251 --> 01:04:23.284
I've been in a bad
place for a while, Nick.


1014
01:04:23.286 --> 01:04:25.220
That's generally the reason

1015
01:04:25.222 --> 01:04:27.622
people pick up hookers
in the first place.


1016
01:04:27.624 --> 01:04:28.723
No, it's not that.

1017
01:04:32.629 --> 01:04:34.562
I think I know what
I need to do now


1018
01:04:35.765 --> 01:04:37.398
and a hooker wasn't
gonna be enough.


1019
01:04:39.870 --> 01:04:41.703
I got some rainy day
money upstairs...


1020
01:04:43.273 --> 01:04:44.305
to get you paid.

1021
01:04:45.375 --> 01:04:46.474
Come with me.

1022
01:04:58.788 --> 01:05:00.288
All right. So, I
kind of understand


1023
01:05:00.290 --> 01:05:02.457
why you don't want people
snooping around up here.


1024
01:05:03.293 --> 01:05:05.827
Well, I think after all
these years my secret is safe.


1025
01:05:06.830 --> 01:05:08.496
I can't believe
I'm even up here.


1026
01:05:08.498 --> 01:05:10.765
You've kept this whole
upstairs from me for so long.


1027
01:05:13.170 --> 01:05:14.669
I almost don't want to show you.

1028
01:05:16.439 --> 01:05:17.439
Show me what?

1029
01:05:18.909 --> 01:05:19.909
Me.

1030
01:05:32.622 --> 01:05:33.888
I know, right?

1031
01:05:36.726 --> 01:05:37.825
What is that?

1032
01:05:39.329 --> 01:05:41.362
I'm trying to figure out
for years, believe me.


1033
01:05:44.834 --> 01:05:45.934
Is it real?

1034
01:05:45.936 --> 01:05:47.936
Yeah.

1035
01:05:52.509 --> 01:05:53.975
Okay.

1036
01:05:53.977 --> 01:05:55.777
All right. Uh...

1037
01:05:57.814 --> 01:05:59.280
Thank you for showing me.

1038
01:06:00.650 --> 01:06:04.452
I... You know, I won't say
anything to anyone about this.


1039
01:06:05.488 --> 01:06:07.488
No, Nick, I know.

1040
01:06:07.490 --> 01:06:08.556
No, Mitch!

1041
01:06:08.558 --> 01:06:09.591
<i>Mitch!</i>

1042
01:06:26.543 --> 01:06:29.577
♫♫♫

1043
01:06:37.487 --> 01:06:42.890
♫♫♫

1044
01:07:07.017 --> 01:07:08.283
Brilliant.

1045
01:07:09.319 --> 01:07:10.752
Fucking brilliant.

1046
01:07:17.827 --> 01:07:22.363
♫♫♫

1047
01:07:41.484 --> 01:07:44.852
♫♫♫

1048
01:08:38.742 --> 01:08:39.742
Hello?

1049
01:08:40.610 --> 01:08:42.009
Who is there?

1050
01:08:42.011 --> 01:08:43.011
Luke?

1051
01:08:43.813 --> 01:08:44.912
Hello?

1052
01:08:50.754 --> 01:08:52.387
Mitch, is that you?

1053
01:09:00.597 --> 01:09:03.030
Shit!

1054
01:09:03.032 --> 01:09:04.399
What's that?

1055
01:09:06.736 --> 01:09:08.703
Okay, okay.

1056
01:09:42.572 --> 01:09:46.073
♫♫♫

1057
01:09:53.483 --> 01:09:55.750
Well, author Mitch Stockridge's
second novel


1058
01:09:55.752 --> 01:09:57.819
is raking in the rave reviews.

1059
01:09:57.821 --> 01:10:00.922
New York Times calls it
ambitious and brilliant.


1060
01:10:00.924 --> 01:10:03.991
The Chicago Tribune
says it's a bold new step


1061
01:10:03.993 --> 01:10:05.460
in truly self-help.

1062
01:10:05.462 --> 01:10:07.495
<i>And the San Francisco
Chronicle says</i>


1063
01:10:07.497 --> 01:10:09.831
<i>it's not only the most
inspirational book</i>


1064
01:10:09.833 --> 01:10:10.898
<i>of the decade,</i>

1065
01:10:10.900 --> 01:10:13.634
<i>it just might be the strongest.</i>

1066
01:10:15.238 --> 01:10:19.507
♫♫♫

1067
01:10:29.853 --> 01:10:31.586
I knew you could do it, Mitch.

1068
01:10:32.222 --> 01:10:34.039
You're a genius.

1069
01:10:34.040 --> 01:10:35.857
No such thing. It's a lot
of hard work and sacrifice.


1070
01:10:35.859 --> 01:10:37.124
Matthew Lopez.

1071
01:10:42.665 --> 01:10:44.265
Next please.

1072
01:10:44.267 --> 01:10:46.868
To Peter Sanchez.

1073
01:10:50.039 --> 01:10:51.739
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.


1074
01:11:07.257 --> 01:11:08.257
Mitch.

1075
01:11:09.993 --> 01:11:11.526
Hey, Laura.

1076
01:11:11.528 --> 01:11:13.828
I see you've got
another book out.


1077
01:11:13.830 --> 01:11:15.796
Congratulations.

1078
01:11:15.798 --> 01:11:18.299
- I'm sure Nick is very proud.
- Thanks. That means a lot.


1079
01:11:18.301 --> 01:11:20.268
Have you heard
anything from Nick?


1080
01:11:20.270 --> 01:11:21.953
No.

1081
01:11:21.954 --> 01:11:23.637
You're his best friend.
He didn't tell you anything?


1082
01:11:23.640 --> 01:11:24.805
I'm sorry.

1083
01:11:24.807 --> 01:11:26.040
Please try to...

1084
01:11:27.010 --> 01:11:28.209
I have to go, Laura.

1085
01:11:39.222 --> 01:11:40.755
You're walking
the beat, Detective?


1086
01:11:40.757 --> 01:11:43.824
Kind of. I was over at
Mitch Stockridge's place.


1087
01:11:43.826 --> 01:11:46.627
Oh, funny story.
You got your warrant.


1088
01:11:48.097 --> 01:11:49.931
Are you kidding me?

1089
01:11:49.933 --> 01:11:52.567
I thought they were gonna
protect this guy forever.


1090
01:11:53.803 --> 01:11:55.002
What did it?

1091
01:11:55.004 --> 01:11:57.004
- The hooker thing?
- Yes.


1092
01:11:57.006 --> 01:12:00.675
Well, it turns out the guy that
bailed your boy out is missing.


1093
01:12:02.645 --> 01:12:04.946
What is it with you
and this author?


1094
01:12:04.948 --> 01:12:06.013
I have to go.

1095
01:12:14.123 --> 01:12:17.325
Look at this,
"ambitious and brilliant."


1096
01:12:18.895 --> 01:12:20.761
It's the New York Times talking.

1097
01:12:21.998 --> 01:12:23.164
You read The Chronicle yet?

1098
01:12:24.367 --> 01:12:25.800
I got through some of them.

1099
01:12:26.836 --> 01:12:28.102
Takes me a while these days.

1100
01:12:30.273 --> 01:12:32.173
Advance sales are
out of the roof.


1101
01:12:32.175 --> 01:12:34.241
It almost makes up for the time

1102
01:12:34.243 --> 01:12:37.712
you left me alone
to go write in a cabin.


1103
01:12:37.714 --> 01:12:39.080
You're still alive.

1104
01:12:40.149 --> 01:12:41.149
Barely.

1105
01:12:44.921 --> 01:12:47.154
Well, Son, you did it.

1106
01:12:47.156 --> 01:12:50.291
- Are you being sarcastic?
- No.


1107
01:12:50.293 --> 01:12:51.626
This time you did it.

1108
01:12:56.366 --> 01:12:57.366
Thanks, Dad.

1109
01:12:58.301 --> 01:12:59.367
It means the world to me.

1110
01:13:02.071 --> 01:13:04.372
Is that what you really
all you were waiting for?


1111
01:13:04.374 --> 01:13:05.840
You really are a mess,
aren't you?


1112
01:13:07.944 --> 01:13:10.177
If you actually thought anything
you've done with your life


1113
01:13:10.179 --> 01:13:11.379
was worth a damn,

1114
01:13:11.381 --> 01:13:13.881
you wouldn't be so
worried about what I felt


1115
01:13:15.084 --> 01:13:17.885
and you wouldn't be so angry
at the world all the time.


1116
01:13:21.290 --> 01:13:22.323
You're right, Dad,

1117
01:13:23.993 --> 01:13:25.760
I don't need to be
angry anymore.


1118
01:13:48.451 --> 01:13:52.687
♫♫♫

1119
01:14:00.063 --> 01:14:04.331
♫♫♫

1120
01:14:19.382 --> 01:14:23.417
♫♫♫

1121
01:14:25.388 --> 01:14:29.123
♫♫♫

1122
01:14:30.226 --> 01:14:31.859
Get down!

1123
01:14:34.864 --> 01:14:36.097
What?

1124
01:14:55.384 --> 01:14:56.884
Thank you so much for the time.

1125
01:15:00.990 --> 01:15:03.057
- Mr. Stockridge.
- Detective.


1126
01:15:03.059 --> 01:15:05.126
It is so nice to see you again.

1127
01:15:05.995 --> 01:15:07.495
I feel like you have
a thing for me.


1128
01:15:07.497 --> 01:15:10.765
Mr. Stockridge, I recently
received a distraught phone call


1129
01:15:10.767 --> 01:15:11.966
from a grieving widow.

1130
01:15:12.802 --> 01:15:14.802
I had nothing new to tell her.

1131
01:15:14.804 --> 01:15:16.537
She had nothing new to tell me.

1132
01:15:16.539 --> 01:15:19.974
- Well, except for one thing.
- And what's that?


1133
01:15:21.511 --> 01:15:23.745
Quite by chance,

1134
01:15:23.746 --> 01:15:25.980
poor Mrs. Brennaman
corroborated Ms. Dettler's story


1135
01:15:25.982 --> 01:15:28.015
about rooms on the second floor

1136
01:15:28.017 --> 01:15:30.451
that no one was
allowed to go in.


1137
01:15:30.453 --> 01:15:31.453
Hmm...

1138
01:15:32.321 --> 01:15:34.021
I see.

1139
01:15:34.023 --> 01:15:36.257
I see, I see, I see.

1140
01:15:37.326 --> 01:15:40.828
- I'm a very private person.
- Mitch, I have a warrant.


1141
01:15:40.830 --> 01:15:43.798
We can do this the easy
way or the hard way.


1142
01:15:43.800 --> 01:15:45.900
I guess you got what you
wanted then, Detective.


1143
01:15:46.836 --> 01:15:48.169
Will there be anything else?

1144
01:15:48.171 --> 01:15:49.904
I need to go meet
with my publisher.


1145
01:15:51.374 --> 01:15:53.407
If you like books,
you're welcome to join us.


1146
01:15:53.409 --> 01:15:58.379
You know I know you never
shed any tears for Luke Rousseau


1147
01:15:58.381 --> 01:16:02.850
and I can accept that you made
yourself not care about any


1148
01:16:02.852 --> 01:16:05.119
or many of the others.

1149
01:16:06.088 --> 01:16:09.990
- Nick Brennaman was your friend.
- And I miss him every day.


1150
01:16:09.992 --> 01:16:11.926
I'll choose to believe that.

1151
01:16:11.927 --> 01:16:13.861
I noticed you made a beeline
for the room upstairs,


1152
01:16:13.863 --> 01:16:16.197
like you knew exactly
what you were looking for.


1153
01:16:18.167 --> 01:16:19.333
I'm not mad.

1154
01:16:19.335 --> 01:16:22.403
I'm just wondering
how much do you know.


1155
01:16:22.405 --> 01:16:24.856
I know enough.

1156
01:16:24.857 --> 01:16:27.308
Well, then you'll know no one's
going to believe your story.


1157
01:16:30.246 --> 01:16:34.148
- You're a monster, Stockridge.
- I take your word for it.


1158
01:16:34.150 --> 01:16:35.516
I help people.

1159
01:16:35.518 --> 01:16:38.319
You remember the woman
from the grocery store.


1160
01:16:38.321 --> 01:16:39.887
She said I saved
her friend's life.


1161
01:16:39.889 --> 01:16:41.856
Even you were impressed.

1162
01:16:41.858 --> 01:16:44.291
You think your books
help everyone, huh?


1163
01:16:46.229 --> 01:16:48.629
Well, guess again,
they didn't help me.


1164
01:16:48.631 --> 01:16:50.865
How? You act like I destroyed
your life or something.


1165
01:16:50.867 --> 01:16:54.869
But you did, Mitch the bitch.

1166
01:16:54.871 --> 01:16:58.539
Your little stories,
inspirational stories


1167
01:16:58.541 --> 01:17:01.175
inspired my husband
to follow his dreams


1168
01:17:01.177 --> 01:17:03.143
and walk out on his family.

1169
01:17:03.145 --> 01:17:05.212
So that's what
this has been about.


1170
01:17:05.214 --> 01:17:10.150
We were happy, happy
and then you ruined everything.


1171
01:17:10.152 --> 01:17:12.219
You'll never know how many
people I actually helped.


1172
01:17:12.221 --> 01:17:13.888
Where is Nick, Mitch?

1173
01:17:13.890 --> 01:17:15.940
He is not here.

1174
01:17:15.941 --> 01:17:17.991
How could you do this
to your best friend?


1175
01:17:17.994 --> 01:17:19.260
You're just projecting.

1176
01:17:19.262 --> 01:17:20.527
- You're a monster.
- Leave.


1177
01:17:21.364 --> 01:17:24.531
You're a selfish piece
of shit and I swear...


1178
01:17:24.533 --> 01:17:27.201
I help people.
My books help people.


1179
01:17:27.203 --> 01:17:30.371
God, keep telling yourself that.

1180
01:17:30.373 --> 01:17:31.906
Goodbye, Detective.

1181
01:17:41.284 --> 01:17:45.519
♫♫♫

1182
01:18:12.348 --> 01:18:14.114
<i>Mitch Stockridge,</i>

1183
01:18:14.116 --> 01:18:15.582
<i>his self-help books
are blowing up.</i>


1184
01:18:15.584 --> 01:18:17.584
<i>I highly recommend...</i>

1185
01:18:17.585 --> 01:18:19.585
<i>You should buy
Mitch Stockridge's book today.</i>


1186
01:18:19.588 --> 01:18:23.190
<i>It's changed my life.
It can change yours.</i>


1187
01:18:23.192 --> 01:18:25.426
Wow, Mitch, you're on time.

1188
01:18:25.428 --> 01:18:27.261
Well, I know how you treat
authors that run late.


1189
01:18:27.263 --> 01:18:30.497
Oh, come on, that's
water under the bridge.


1190
01:18:30.499 --> 01:18:31.732
Would you actually have sued me?

1191
01:18:31.734 --> 01:18:35.169
What? You gotta do
what you gotta do, Mitch,


1192
01:18:35.171 --> 01:18:37.171
to get ahead these days.

1193
01:18:37.173 --> 01:18:38.572
Yeah, you're right there.

1194
01:18:38.574 --> 01:18:41.608
Can I get you something?
Coffee, biscotti?


1195
01:18:41.610 --> 01:18:43.477
The book must be selling well.
You're being nice.


1196
01:18:43.479 --> 01:18:46.480
Well, of course, I'm being nice.
You're back on top, Mitch.


1197
01:18:46.482 --> 01:18:51.018
You've got everything
you ever wanted, you know.


1198
01:18:51.020 --> 01:18:53.053
God, you must be so proud.

1199
01:18:53.055 --> 01:18:54.055
I am.

1200
01:18:55.024 --> 01:18:56.490
And you're fired.

1201
01:18:57.426 --> 01:18:59.243
Excuse me?

1202
01:18:59.244 --> 01:19:01.061
Don't take it, personal.
You know how it is.


1203
01:19:01.063 --> 01:19:02.396
You've got to do
what you've got to do


1204
01:19:02.398 --> 01:19:04.131
to get ahead these days.

1205
01:19:04.133 --> 01:19:05.666
Oh, come on, Mitch.
Let's talk about...


1206
01:19:05.668 --> 01:19:08.402
- There's nothing to talk about.
- Don't be angry.


1207
01:19:09.739 --> 01:19:11.338
That's the funny thing.

1208
01:19:11.340 --> 01:19:13.741
I'm not angry. I'm happy.

1209
01:19:16.278 --> 01:19:17.411
Good luck, Natalie.

1210
01:19:22.051 --> 01:19:23.183
Bastard.

1211
01:19:28.224 --> 01:19:30.457
<i>We have
Author Mitch Stockridge with us</i>


1212
01:19:30.459 --> 01:19:33.427
hot off the success
of<i>Sorry, Not Sorry.</i>


1213
01:19:33.429 --> 01:19:35.596
- Mitch, you got a second?
- Absolutely.


1214
01:19:35.598 --> 01:19:37.598
Glad to be here
supporting the cause.


1215
01:19:37.600 --> 01:19:40.835
Great.

1216
01:19:40.836 --> 01:19:44.071
We would all love to know where
do you get your ideas from?


1217
01:19:45.107 --> 01:19:46.573
Believe it or not,
I get it a lot.


1218
01:19:48.644 --> 01:19:50.811
Well, it's sort of like this:

1219
01:19:50.813 --> 01:19:53.547
Ever since I was a little kid
I've been haunted by a monster


1220
01:19:53.549 --> 01:19:56.283
and I feed it
sacrifices of people


1221
01:19:56.285 --> 01:19:59.119
and, in return, it spits out
an outline for a best-seller


1222
01:19:59.121 --> 01:20:01.388
and I just can't stop.

1223
01:20:02.792 --> 01:20:03.792
Uh...

1224
01:20:05.161 --> 01:20:09.363
Okay, well that's
why you're a writer.


1225
01:20:09.365 --> 01:20:12.366
All right then. Wow.

1226
01:20:53.776 --> 01:20:57.344
Damn!

1227
01:21:16.232 --> 01:21:17.264
Hello?